newsArray.title: IND vs BAN Live Score, T20 World Cup 2024: Upbeat India Face off Against Desperate Bangladesh
creator: ABP News Bureau
newsArray.description: IND vs BAN Live Score, T20 World Cup 2024: Welcome to ABP Live‚Äôs live blog of the India vs Bangladesh T20 World Cup 2024 Super 8 match. The Men in Blue will face off against the Bangla Tigers in a crucial Super 8 stage match as the race to the T20 World Cup 2024 semi-finals intensifies. This will be the second Super 8 match for both the teams and India will be coming off an emphatic win over Afghanistan in their first Super 8 match.Bangladesh, on the other hand, will be coming off a defeat at the hands of the 2021 T20 World Cup champions Australia in their last encounter. If India seal another victory here, they will all but confirm their berth in the semi-finals of the tournament. Whereas, Bangladesh find themselves in a must-win situation as a loss against India will almost knock them out of the prestigious tournament.Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma getting in a net session ahead of India's #T20WorldCup clash against Bangladesh üëÄ pic.twitter.com/1U8SDeify5‚Äî T20 World Cup (@T20WorldCup) June 22, 2024Much anticipation surrounded the opening pair of Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli ahead of the World Cup, but the partnership has underperformed. Kohli has managed only 28 runs in 4 innings, and Rohit has struggled after his half-century against Ireland. In contrast, India's bowling attack, spearheaded by Jasprit Bumrah, has been outstanding and crucial to their victories. Pacer Arshdeep Singh has also shown excellent form, and Hardik Pandya has provided the Indian captain with valuable flexibility.IND vs BAN T20 World Cup 2024 Super 8 Match Probable Playing 11sIndia Probable Playing 11: Rohit Sharma (c), Virat Kohli, Rishabh Pant (wk), Suryakumar Yadav, Shivam Dube, Hardik Pandya, Ravindra Jadeja, Axar Patel, Kuldeep Yadav, Jasprit Bumrah, Arshdeep SinghBangladesh Probable Playing 11: Tanzid Hasan Tamim, Najmul Hossain Shanto (c), Litton Kumar Das, Shakib al Hasan, Towhid Hridoy, Mahmudullah, Jaker Ali, Rishad Hossain, Taskin Ahmed, Mustafizur Rahman and Tanzim Shakib.
